TY  - JOUR
AU  - Warner, John T.
AU  - Poindexter, J. Carl, Jr.
AU  - Fearn, Robert M.
T1  - Employer-Employee Interaction and the Duration of Unemployment1
PY  - 1980
Y1  - 1980/03/01
DO  - 10.2307/1884538
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 94
IS  - 2
SP  - 211
EP  - 233
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper identifies three alternative approaches to the duration of unemployment—the screening, the formal search theory, and the intensity of search approaches. From these approaches, a unified model of the weekly probability of leaving unemployment (WPOLU) is developed. In this model, WPOLU is the product of the weekly probability of job vacancy location, the probability of offer extension, and the probability of offer acceptance. The determinants of these probabilities are analyzed. The model is tested with data from the 1970 Census Employment Survey. Evidence supporting all three approaches is found. An eclectic view of unemployment is called for.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1884538
ER  - 



