TY  - JOUR
AU  - Nakao, Takeo
T1  - Demand Growth, Profitability, and Entry*
PY  - 1980
Y1  - 1980/03/01
DO  - 10.2307/1884547
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 94
IS  - 2
SP  - 397
EP  - 411
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The purpose of this paper is to elucidate on the effect of demand growth on the competitive structure of an industry. We describe the effects of growth of market demand on concentration, barriers to entry, and the rate of return on capital. To illustrate these effects, we examine the behavior of an established firm in a fast growing industry, formulating an entry decision model of a potential firm. Our model lends support to the view that the increase in the growth rate of demand increases the dominant firm's profit rate, but decreases its market share.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1884547
ER  - 



